WEBVTT

00:00.510 --> 00:02.970
Huh? You found a hundred yen?

00:02.970 --> 00:05.290
How old are you?

00:05.290 --> 00:06.230
What?

00:06.590 --> 00:10.380
Um, I'm eighteen. Why?

00:11.490 --> 00:12.990
Tokyo Police
2nd District Police Station

00:13.280 --> 00:17.340
Don't meet a lot of people 
that honest these days.

00:17.820 --> 00:20.750
Stupidly honest, you might say.

00:17.830 --> 00:22.330
Nao Kanzaki

00:22.580 --> 00:24.680
"Stupidly honest Nao."

00:24.680 --> 00:27.310
That's what people always called me.

00:28.090 --> 00:30.830
But I never let it bother me.

00:31.380 --> 00:35.320
After all, my father named me Nao

00:35.320 --> 00:37.840
because he wanted me 
to be an honest girl.

00:39.930 --> 00:41.740
Package delivery.

00:45.250 --> 00:47.150
I don't remember ordering anything.

00:47.830 --> 00:51.690
The sender is... "LGT Office."

00:52.530 --> 00:53.530
What is this?

00:55.610 --> 01:07.290
Ms. Nao Kanzaki,
 Congratulations.
 You have beaten the 1-in-100,000 odds
to participate in the Liar Game Tournament.

00:56.790 --> 01:01.880
"You have beaten the 1-in-100,000 odds

01:01.880 --> 01:06.340
to participate in the 
Liar Game Tournament."

01:07.680 --> 01:08.830
Huh...

01:09.820 --> 01:12.130
Thinking back now,

01:12.130 --> 01:16.800
I really should have thought a lot more 
carefully before opening that box.

01:20.230 --> 01:21.950
Th-This is...

01:25.020 --> 01:29.480
The Legendary Con Artist

01:25.340 --> 01:29.480
Eighty, ninety, a hundred...

01:29.810 --> 01:32.150
A hundred million yen, and it's real!

01:33.080 --> 01:35.490
If you are hearing this message,

01:33.640 --> 01:35.490
Wh-What's that?!

01:35.490 --> 01:40.240
it means that you are now an official 
participant in the Liar Game.

01:40.240 --> 01:42.310
This decision cannot be reversed.

01:42.690 --> 01:48.290
The enclosed 100 million yen is your 
game money for the first round.

01:48.960 --> 01:52.140
What in the world is the Liar Game?

01:53.160 --> 01:55.090
The rules are simple.

01:53.250 --> 01:55.090
100 Million Yen Battle

01:55.090 --> 02:01.050
Take your opponent's game money
 by any means necessary.

02:01.050 --> 02:03.940
Participation in this game 
is by mutual consent.

02:03.940 --> 02:07.600
No actions taken in the theft of game 
money will be considered criminal.

02:08.110 --> 02:10.340
This is a one-on-one battle.

02:10.340 --> 02:15.210
The game begins the moment you are 
informed of your opponent's identity.

02:15.210 --> 02:18.710
The game will end thirty days thereafter.

02:18.710 --> 02:21.500
Whoever has more game money 
at that time will be the winner.

02:22.120 --> 02:23.610
Once the game is over,

02:23.610 --> 02:26.650
a representative of the LGT Office
will come to collect the game money.

02:26.650 --> 02:31.860
The serial numbers of the 100 million yen
 must match those of your starting pool.

02:32.290 --> 02:35.820
Please return this to the 
representative on arrival.

02:35.820 --> 02:38.030
If you have stolen game 
money from your opponent,

02:38.030 --> 02:40.630
you will be allowed to keep the excess.

02:40.630 --> 02:45.940
In other words, it is possible to win 
up to 100 million yen in this game.

02:45.940 --> 02:48.780
Conversely, if you have 
lost any game money,

02:48.780 --> 02:52.640
you will be forced to pay the difference, 
even if that leaves you in debt.

02:53.450 --> 02:56.630
If I lose, I could end up 
100 million yen in debt?

02:58.090 --> 03:00.030
My mind was spinning.

03:00.330 --> 03:02.960
Not with dreams of the 
incredible money I could win,

03:03.410 --> 03:07.300
but with the fear of ending up
 100 million yen in debt.

03:09.430 --> 03:13.910
What do I do? Who could I even talk to?

03:14.700 --> 03:16.680
The only family I had in the world...

03:18.850 --> 03:21.840
was fighting terminal cancer 
in a care facility.

03:22.440 --> 03:24.180
Hey, Dad. How are you feeling?

03:24.480 --> 03:28.180
Very well. Thanks to the 
lovely weather, I suppose.

03:28.530 --> 03:30.360
Oh, I'm glad.

03:30.360 --> 03:35.880
They said they weren't sure 
he'd make it to New Year's.

03:36.930 --> 03:41.940
Hey there. Is something bothering you?

03:41.940 --> 03:45.210
Huh? No, everything's going great!

03:45.510 --> 03:47.110
I'm even getting used to school.

03:46.920 --> 03:49.170
My one trivial hope in this world...

03:47.110 --> 03:49.170
Every day is fun!

03:49.960 --> 03:53.970
was to make my father's final days

03:53.970 --> 03:57.890
as peaceful and quiet as possible.

03:59.250 --> 04:02.430
I couldn't tell him.

04:03.470 --> 04:04.970
Mitsuo Tanimura Law Office

04:04.970 --> 04:08.090
There's nothing you can do 
about this at the moment.

04:08.090 --> 04:08.820
What?!

04:08.820 --> 04:14.490
It's a lawyer's job to help people 
who've suffered some kind of damages.

04:14.490 --> 04:18.310
But you haven't suffered 
any damages, have you?

04:19.650 --> 04:22.010
If a lawyer can't help me...

04:22.880 --> 04:25.820
I know! If I take it to the police...

04:27.570 --> 04:31.090
That's probably exactly 
what the sender wants.

04:31.090 --> 04:31.900
What?!

04:31.900 --> 04:38.480
I mean, wouldn't most folks go to the cops
 rather than risk winding up in trouble?

04:38.480 --> 04:39.510
Yes!

04:39.510 --> 04:42.780
But it says right here in the rules

04:42.780 --> 04:45.390
that the player must return the game money

04:45.390 --> 04:49.040
to the representative on arrival.

04:49.040 --> 04:54.350
But if you take it to the police,
they'll treat it like a lost article.

04:54.350 --> 04:56.490
That's the trap!

04:56.770 --> 04:58.740
When it comes time to collect

04:58.740 --> 05:01.660
and you tell 'em, "The owner is back, 
so please return the money,"

05:01.660 --> 05:03.980
you think the police will give it to you?

05:05.210 --> 05:09.690
Police only return lost articles 
to whoever lost them.

05:10.250 --> 05:16.070
So when the office shows up as the owner
and claims that money from the police,

05:16.070 --> 05:19.740
they're gonna say you owe them 100 mil!

05:20.140 --> 05:23.750
That's awful... This is like a scam.

05:23.750 --> 05:25.630
Isn't there anything I can do?

05:26.420 --> 05:29.760
Nothing at this point, like I said.

05:30.330 --> 05:33.420
Then who should I talk to?

05:33.420 --> 05:37.820
For advice on a con, 
it's best to talk to a con artist.

05:38.320 --> 05:41.070
Isn't there anything 
more useful you can—

05:41.070 --> 05:43.270
Well, that's your hour up.

05:43.750 --> 05:47.930
Moving forward, 
it'll be 15,000 yen an hour.

05:47.930 --> 05:49.530
What do you say?

05:53.590 --> 05:56.540
What in the world is the Liar Game?

05:58.330 --> 06:00.710
Why would they do this to people?

06:01.510 --> 06:03.410
Why would they choose me?

06:24.230 --> 06:28.050
"Your opponent for the first round 
of the Liar Game has been selected."

06:28.720 --> 06:32.030
"Your opponent is the player enclosed."

06:33.410 --> 06:34.660
I know this man!

06:35.010 --> 06:36.760
That's Fujisawa-sensei!

06:39.180 --> 06:40.670
What a shock.

06:41.160 --> 06:43.590
He was my homeroom teacher 
in middle school.

06:43.590 --> 06:47.200
He helped me when my dad got sick and 
with deciding what high school to attend.

06:47.200 --> 06:49.160
He's such a kind teacher...

06:50.530 --> 06:52.210
I can work with him!

06:52.670 --> 06:54.950
Talk about a lucky break.

06:54.950 --> 06:57.550
Never thought you'd be my opponent!

06:57.550 --> 06:59.000
I feel the same!

06:59.450 --> 07:01.350
By the way, Kanzaki-kun...

07:01.760 --> 07:06.040
You don't honestly think this 
is a real game where people

07:06.040 --> 07:10.150
are chosen at random to 
play for money, do you?

07:10.150 --> 07:11.800
You don't think it is?

07:11.800 --> 07:13.690
Absolutely not.

07:14.370 --> 07:19.790
This is a sham game that 
neither player can ever win.

07:19.790 --> 07:21.200
What?!

07:21.410 --> 07:25.840
Let's say you were up 
against a complete stranger.

07:25.840 --> 07:30.350
If the 100 million went missing 
while you were asleep,

07:30.350 --> 07:32.880
you'd assume he took it, right?

07:33.500 --> 07:34.730
Yes.

07:34.730 --> 07:40.360
But what if it was the Liar Game 
Tournament Office that took it?

07:41.850 --> 07:46.600
They easily could. They have the names 
and home addresses of all the players.

07:46.880 --> 07:51.380
But each player would assume
that their opponent was the culprit.

07:51.730 --> 07:57.380
Then, when the game is over,
they're both 100 million in debt.

07:58.290 --> 07:59.720
That's horrible.

07:59.720 --> 08:04.630
If not for you, I definitely would 
have fallen for their trick.

08:05.550 --> 08:09.700
Now that you see that, let's 
move the money somewhere safe!

08:10.240 --> 08:15.880
The executive office could be
 going after yours as we speak!

08:17.740 --> 08:18.640
It's still here!

08:19.110 --> 08:20.840
Thank goodness.

08:20.260 --> 08:23.270
Looks like they haven't made 
their move just yet.

08:23.270 --> 08:26.400
Sensei, what should I do with it?

08:27.180 --> 08:30.540
The smartest thing would 
be to store it with mine

08:30.540 --> 08:34.460
in a safe deposit box at the 
bank until the game is over.

08:34.460 --> 08:36.170
Great idea!

08:36.170 --> 08:38.840
I'll make the arrangements.

08:38.840 --> 08:42.180
I'll accept full responsibility 
for ensuring the money's safety.

08:42.860 --> 08:44.250
Please take care of it.

08:55.430 --> 08:58.290
At last, I can get a good night's sleep.

09:05.110 --> 09:08.890
How long was I out?

09:14.500 --> 09:15.590
What is this?

09:16.280 --> 09:23.160
Progress Report

09:16.280 --> 09:23.160
Kazuo Fujisawa

09:16.280 --> 09:23.160
Nao Kanzaki

09:16.280 --> 09:23.160
You are currently losing. The game will end in 29 days.

09:17.100 --> 09:19.780
"Liar Game Progress Report."

09:20.320 --> 09:22.680
"You are currently losing."

09:24.490 --> 09:26.000
What in the world?

09:26.900 --> 09:30.540
Oh, so that's their play, is it?

09:31.100 --> 09:35.540
I suspect they've realized 
we know each other.

09:35.540 --> 09:39.290
They can't scam us if we work together,

09:39.830 --> 09:43.630
so they sent you that card 
to sow distrust.

09:44.190 --> 09:45.690
I see.

09:46.690 --> 09:50.430
But of course I still trust you, Sensei!

09:50.430 --> 09:52.230
I know that, dear.

09:52.440 --> 09:54.730
Fujisawa-sensei

09:54.970 --> 09:57.420
I feel so silly for saying that...

09:58.190 --> 09:59.560
I know!

10:00.150 --> 10:03.500
I'll go to his house 
and apologize in person.

10:06.820 --> 10:10.610
Yeah, that's right! A hundred million!

10:10.610 --> 10:12.680
Enough to pay off my debts in one go!

10:12.680 --> 10:14.730
Is he talking about the Liar Game?

10:15.460 --> 10:21.380
My opponent? One of my students 
from five years ago!

10:21.380 --> 10:24.230
She's as honest as they come.

10:24.230 --> 10:26.730
She bought it hook, line, and sinker.

10:26.730 --> 10:29.720
She doesn't even realize
 I stole her hundred million!

10:31.290 --> 10:33.890
She's stupidly honest.

10:45.330 --> 10:46.830
Progress Report

10:45.330 --> 10:46.830
Kazuo Fujisawa

10:45.330 --> 10:46.830
Nao Kanzaki

10:45.330 --> 10:46.830
You are currently losing. The game will end in 29 days.

10:47.770 --> 10:49.030
"Liar"?

10:50.500 --> 10:51.720
One who lies...

10:53.610 --> 10:54.520
It can't be!

10:55.710 --> 10:58.730
That's it. He...

11:00.600 --> 11:02.220
He tricked me!

11:12.250 --> 11:16.420
At last, I realized what had happened.

11:24.390 --> 11:26.060
I have to get it back...

11:27.210 --> 11:31.080
I have to get that 100 million back!

11:32.950 --> 11:37.370
For advice on a con, 
it's best to talk to a con artist.

11:38.410 --> 11:40.100
A con artist...

11:47.010 --> 11:48.580
<u>The Latest on Massive Scam
</u>Genius Con Artist to Be Released Soon

11:48.580 --> 11:50.020
<u>The Latest on Massive Scam
Genius Con Artist to Be Released Soon</u>

11:50.200 --> 11:52.250
Genius Con Artist to Be Released Soon

11:51.040 --> 11:54.020
The genius con artist

11:54.520 --> 11:58.380
who took down the corrupt business
 network Shuei Corporation,

11:58.380 --> 12:03.340
Shinichi Akiyama, 
will soon complete his sentence.

12:00.530 --> 12:05.030
Shinichi Akiyama, soon to be released

12:06.030 --> 12:07.540
Should be just about time.

12:10.040 --> 12:10.850
That him?

12:11.400 --> 12:14.600
No, it's a different convict.

12:16.770 --> 12:18.310
Excuse us.

12:19.230 --> 12:22.170
Could we ask you to get going?

12:22.170 --> 12:24.270
Where's Akiyama?

12:24.270 --> 12:25.750
He's been released.

12:25.750 --> 12:27.690
But that wasn't him.

12:27.970 --> 12:31.550
Akiyama is a master of disguise, you know.

12:33.310 --> 12:34.510
He tricked us!

12:34.510 --> 12:36.830
After him! We can still make it!

12:40.510 --> 12:44.700
Nice work driving them off, Akiyama.

12:47.130 --> 12:48.620
What will I do?!

12:49.330 --> 12:50.990
Where's the way in?

12:50.990 --> 12:53.160
How could I get lost now, of all times?

12:56.950 --> 12:58.890
Ow...

13:00.120 --> 13:02.140
I-I'm so sorry.

13:02.570 --> 13:03.370
Um...

13:06.700 --> 13:08.520
Are you Akiyama-san?!

13:11.330 --> 13:13.030
You've got the wrong guy.

13:13.030 --> 13:14.420
Wait!

13:15.510 --> 13:18.760
Please, help me!

13:19.270 --> 13:22.990
I was betrayed by someone I trusted.

13:24.470 --> 13:27.760
He took 100 million yen from me.

13:30.580 --> 13:33.680
There's nothing I can do to help you.

13:34.480 --> 13:37.230
Talk to the cops or a lawyer or something.

13:37.790 --> 13:39.090
I can't!

13:39.520 --> 13:42.410
You're the only person who can help me!

13:44.910 --> 13:48.970
Do you realize what you're saying?

13:49.800 --> 13:52.620
You're asking a man 
who just got out of prison

13:52.620 --> 13:55.260
to help you steal 100 million yen.

13:55.800 --> 14:00.020
Even if someone scammed you out of it, 
stealing that money back is theft.

14:00.860 --> 14:05.050
You're asking me to get 
myself arrested again!

14:06.120 --> 14:07.590
Well...

14:28.130 --> 14:30.470
How long are you going to follow me?

14:30.470 --> 14:33.600
Until you hear me out.

14:35.440 --> 14:38.980
Fine. I'll listen to your story, at least.

14:39.600 --> 14:42.840
I'm going to drop my stuff off
 at my place, so just wait there.

14:43.260 --> 14:44.800
Wait right there.

14:45.490 --> 14:46.540
Okay!

14:47.230 --> 14:51.470
Izakaya Yocchan
Japanese Sake,
 Shochu, Craft Beer

14:54.250 --> 14:55.770
Thanks for coming.

14:57.180 --> 14:59.580
He's been gone a while...

15:02.000 --> 15:03.550
She's still waiting?

15:04.790 --> 15:07.000
Izakaya Yocchan

15:05.410 --> 15:07.000
Hey!

15:07.000 --> 15:09.260
Let's have some fun, girlie.

15:09.260 --> 15:11.660
I'm waiting for someone.

15:11.660 --> 15:14.020
Come on. You've been here for hours.

15:14.020 --> 15:19.220
I think you're looking for a man 
who'll really rock your world—

15:19.580 --> 15:21.160
Akiyama-san!

15:21.160 --> 15:22.970
Sorry for the long wait.

15:23.220 --> 15:24.290
Let's go.

15:24.700 --> 15:25.610
Okay!

15:26.610 --> 15:28.610
Strawberry au Lait

15:26.610 --> 15:28.610
Umeboshi Rice Ball

15:26.610 --> 15:28.610
Coarse Red Bean Bun

15:30.130 --> 15:31.790
You can really pack it in.

15:33.270 --> 15:36.330
I didn't have anything to eat 
the whole time I was waiting.

15:36.820 --> 15:39.670
Why the hell not? You could've passed out.

15:39.670 --> 15:42.880
But you told me to wait right there...

15:43.980 --> 15:49.150
Seriously? Most people would get
 the hint after a couple of hours.

15:49.150 --> 15:51.500
Huh? What did you just say?

15:53.530 --> 15:56.880
You're stupidly honest. 
This is why you got scammed.

16:00.340 --> 16:03.590
Is it wrong to be stupidly honest?

16:06.500 --> 16:09.420
Tell me about your 100 million.

16:12.050 --> 16:14.210
The Liar Game, huh?

16:14.210 --> 16:17.170
Seems hard to believe, but...

16:17.970 --> 16:19.700
What do you want to do?

16:20.290 --> 16:22.140
Win the game?

16:22.140 --> 16:25.360
Or wash your hands of the 
whole shady business?

16:26.490 --> 16:28.020
I want out!

16:28.020 --> 16:31.730
I just want to get back my 
100 million and call it a day!

16:32.310 --> 16:34.300
That's simple, then.

16:34.300 --> 16:38.910
We'll tell your teacher how you feel 
and get him to return your money.

16:42.810 --> 16:46.250
Hey, Kanzaki-kun. Who's that with you?

16:46.840 --> 16:48.070
Sensei...

16:48.480 --> 16:52.710
Will you please return 
my 100 million now?

16:53.440 --> 16:55.560
Where's this coming from?

16:55.560 --> 16:59.030
I told you, it's in a safe at the bank.

16:59.030 --> 17:02.940
The safe can only be accessed 
during the bank's business hours.

17:02.940 --> 17:07.950
And for your safety, it's best to 
keep it there until the game's over.

17:08.380 --> 17:11.150
I overheard you...

17:11.150 --> 17:13.840
What you said on the telephone.

17:14.470 --> 17:18.630
That you'd scammed 100 million 
yen from a student.

17:19.040 --> 17:22.680
D-Don't know what you're talking about!

17:22.680 --> 17:24.820
I'll keep this brief.

17:25.530 --> 17:27.950
Return her 100 million.

17:28.470 --> 17:32.610
Do it by tomorrow, or we're 
taking you to the police.

17:32.610 --> 17:34.540
Th-The police?!

17:34.540 --> 17:37.490
This is just a game! 
It's there in the rules!

17:37.490 --> 17:40.360
Any game money taken 
isn't considered a crime!

17:40.890 --> 17:44.120
So you acknowledge that this is a game?

17:45.630 --> 17:48.870
You see all of this as a game.

17:48.870 --> 17:52.510
Which is why you tricked her 
and took her 100 million.

18:01.380 --> 18:04.160
That's right! I tricked her!

18:04.160 --> 18:07.040
But you're in no position 
to criticize me for it!

18:07.040 --> 18:09.890
Because this is all just a game!

18:09.890 --> 18:15.150
If I hadn't taken her 100 million, 
she might have taken mine!

18:15.150 --> 18:17.410
I would never do that!

18:17.810 --> 18:23.050
I don't believe you. 
People just aren't trustworthy.

18:23.740 --> 18:28.510
I was in charge of class trips
 at my old school.

18:28.920 --> 18:33.270
Every year, I booked with 
the same travel agency,

18:33.270 --> 18:38.540
and the head of the agency paid me 
a small kickback as a thank-you.

18:38.920 --> 18:44.170
But one year, they said they 
weren't going to pay me.

18:44.170 --> 18:47.730
And when I said I'd use another agency,

18:47.730 --> 18:52.390
the bastards snitched on me 
to the board of education!

18:54.440 --> 18:56.940
I was fired on the spot.

18:57.330 --> 19:00.690
My family left me.

19:00.690 --> 19:03.350
That's just what people do!

19:03.350 --> 19:05.700
When you trust them,
 they make a fool of you!

19:05.700 --> 19:08.660
But then I got the message 
about the Liar Game.

19:08.660 --> 19:12.700
"I'm saved. There really 
is a God," I thought.

19:12.700 --> 19:17.080
So I have to win this game!

19:17.080 --> 19:20.470
Don't say that! Please help me, Sensei!

19:20.470 --> 19:22.620
My father has terminal cancer.

19:22.620 --> 19:27.010
I just want to make sure
 his final days are peaceful.

19:27.580 --> 19:31.720
If I end up 100 million in debt now...

19:31.720 --> 19:33.970
I don't give a damn!

19:33.970 --> 19:37.200
I don't give a damn about your dad!

19:37.200 --> 19:41.410
I don't give a damn 
about anyone but myself!

19:42.250 --> 19:47.490
Well, good luck thinking of a way
 to get the 100 million back.

19:52.500 --> 19:55.860
Hard to believe he was ever a teacher.

19:57.160 --> 19:59.730
Money really changes people.

19:59.730 --> 20:02.580
I've seen more than my share
 of that in the past.

20:05.610 --> 20:08.030
Crying won't get you out of this.

20:08.740 --> 20:15.510
A teacher I trusted put me
100 million yen in debt!

20:16.190 --> 20:19.480
You're not actually in debt yet.

20:19.930 --> 20:23.650
But the money's stowed 
in a safe deposit box.

20:24.160 --> 20:25.710
A safe deposit box...

20:26.190 --> 20:30.700
Ironically, Fujisawa just 
exposed his own weakness.

20:32.010 --> 20:33.410
His weakness?

20:34.440 --> 20:39.280
Safe deposit boxes can only be
 accessed when the bank is open.

20:40.370 --> 20:42.670
How long does the game last?

20:43.450 --> 20:45.950
There's 23 days left.

20:45.950 --> 20:50.120
So it ends on June 14th... A Sunday.

20:46.930 --> 20:50.930
Game Ends

20:52.670 --> 20:55.540
No one's getting into the safe that day.

20:56.440 --> 21:01.720
He'd have to take the money 
out by 5:00 that Friday.

21:02.290 --> 21:06.950
Which means it'll be out of the safe 
for two days before the deadline!

21:07.650 --> 21:10.070
In other words, this isn't over yet.

21:11.570 --> 21:17.410
But even once the money's out of the safe,
it won't be easy to steal, will it?

21:17.720 --> 21:20.780
Don't worry. I have a plan.

21:21.160 --> 21:22.750
Really?!

21:22.750 --> 21:25.380
Wait, does that mean...

21:26.220 --> 21:30.670
Akiyama-san, you're going to help me?!

21:31.390 --> 21:35.840
I refuse to be an accomplice to a crime,

21:35.840 --> 21:39.110
but Fujisawa admitted 
that this was just a game.

21:40.250 --> 21:46.110
If it's just a game, and you're ready to
do what it takes to steal his 100 million,

21:46.800 --> 21:48.260
I'm happy to help you.

21:50.390 --> 21:53.030
I am ready.

21:54.940 --> 21:56.990
I don't work cheap.

21:56.990 --> 21:58.640
We split your gains evenly.

21:58.640 --> 22:02.240
Meaning if we steal the whole pot,
 I expect 50 million.

22:04.290 --> 22:07.410
Thank you so much! It's a deal!

22:07.410 --> 22:09.240
Keep your voice down, stupid.

23:45.060 --> 23:50.100
Next Time

23:45.060 --> 23:50.100
Shockwave
